text.tspan: 6.2.7MAIN ENGINE AND AUX. ENGINE REPORTSPerformance reports such as main engine and auxiliary engine reports and maintenance reports such as Crank webs deflection,bearing measurement reports, liner/piston calibration reports and auxiliary engine overhauling reports shall serve as a basis forverifying the operating condition of the main and auxiliary engines and the wear rate of the various components. Suitable actions asdeemed necessary, such as increasing/ decreasing feed rate of cylinder lubrication, renewal of cylinder liners, etc., shall thereafter betaken.6.2.8OTHER AUXILIARY EQUIPMENT AND MACHINERYOther auxiliary machinery and equipment shall be periodically opened up for inspection by the ship’s staff as per the plannedmaintenance system, to verify the condition of their components. Besides the above, their performance shall be assessed by judgingthe parameters such as pressure, discharge rate, etc.6.3PLANNED MAINTENANCE SYSTEM (PMS)In order to achieve the required maintenance standard of the vessels and its equipment and monitor same a Computerised Planned Maintenance System module inPhoenix software, is provided on all vessels.The maintenance plan shall use preventive measures which shall include measures such as, use of vibration, infrared or performance monitoring of main andauxiliary equipment.As and when any maintenance or repairs are carried out a brief summary of the work done is entered in the PMS system.Jobs should be planned and carried out within the due dates indicated in the PMS so that they do not have to be postponed or become overdue.Postponement of maintenance routines are to be dealt with, depending on the priority assigned to the jobs, as follows:Priority 1: Normally postponement is not permitted. In exceptional circumstances this may be permitted subject to Risk Assessment and office approval.Priority 2: Normally postponement is not permitted. In exceptional circumstances this may be permitted subject to office approval up to a maximum of 30 days.Further extension requires Risk Assessment.Priority 3: Can be postponed by Chief Engineer / Chief Officer up to a maximum of 30 days. If the period exceeds 30 days, approval of Technical Superintendent isrequired who may allow the same after due consultation with the General Manager. When requesting postponement, vessel must provide an assessment of thecondition of the equipment.Status of jobs carried out and due jobs can be checked by the Superintendent in charge in the office and verified during his routine inspection of the vessel.6.4CRITICAL EQUIPMENT AND SYSTEMSCritical Equipment and Systems are any ship based equipment, operating system or alarm, failure or damage of which may place theship or its crew at risk, could lead to an accident or seriously affect the seaworthiness of the ship.Critical equipment and systems on board are to be identified, tested and maintained to ensure functional reliability.A risk assessment is to be carried out for the identification of Critical equipment and systems for specific vessel types.While carrying out the Risk Assessment the following factors shall, as a minimum, be taken into account:1) Type of vessel2) Type of the equipment3) Redundancy of the equipment such as duplication / stand by units / alternate arrangements.4) Consequence of failure of the equipment.5) Controls / measures that are available to mitigate the risk.Critical Equipment and Systems applicable to each vessel are identified in the vessel’s Planned Maintenance System.6.4.1RISK ASSESSMENT FOR IDENTIFICATION OF CRITICAL EQUIPMENT AND ENVIRONMENTALLY CRITICALEQUIPMENT.The following is the procedure to be followed:1. Type of VesselIdentify the various ship types2. Equipment NameIn this column the equipment applicable to the ship type is listed.3. DP / Non-DP RelatedIn this column equipment applicable to the ship type is listed.4. ServiceThe service or purpose of the equipment is identified in this column.5. Determine consequence of failure of the equipment which is a sum of the following: a) Risk to Ship or Crew - Slight(1), Moderate(3) or Severe(5)
